<p id="d1e2922">A challenge to NIPA dynamic prior is the unavailability of the contact network in the future. Hence, we assume the traffic matrix to remain constant after the last observation point 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e2925" display="inline" altimg="si17.svg">
   <mi>n</mi>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>: 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e2930" display="inline" altimg="si111.svg">
   <mrow>
    <msub>
     <mrow>
      <mi>B</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mtext>prior</mtext>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mrow>
     <mo>[</mo>
     <mi>n</mi>
     <mo>+</mo>
     <mi>k</mi>
     <mo>]</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak" linebreakstyle="after">=</mo>
    <msub>
     <mrow>
      <mi>B</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mtext>prior</mtext>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mrow>
     <mo>[</mo>
     <mi>n</mi>
     <mo>]</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> for all 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e2968" display="inline" altimg="si112.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi>k</mi>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak" linebreakstyle="after">&gt;</mo>
    <mn>0</mn>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>.
</p>
